{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDS"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Tokens","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"About responsabilities:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"mermaid","code":["flowchart TD","    A(Raw token) --> |Contains primitive type SwiftUI value| B(Semantic token)","    B --> |Brings higher logic and functional meanings|C(Component token)","    C --> |Helps to make match between View and semantics|D(Component)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example:"}]},{"syntax":"mermaid","code":["flowchart TD","    A(colorFunctionalDodgerBlue500) --> |#26B2FF| B(sysColorBrandInformationDefault)","    B --> C(.informationIconbackgroundColor)","    C --> D(InformationModalView)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can have the graphical rendering of this "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mermaid","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" charts in the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/blob\/develop\/OUDS\/README.md"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Frustrated? Boost "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-docc\/issues\/1026","isActive":true}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Component tokens","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Component-tokens"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") are defined for components yet."}]},{"text":"Semantic tokens","type":"heading","anchor":"Semantic-tokens","level":2},{"level":3,"text":"What they are","type":"heading","anchor":"What-they-are"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"These ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" (","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/","isActive":true},{"text":") can be used mainly for ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"component tokens","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to apply some style and configuration values."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"They can be seen as an high level of usage with functional meanings.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A semantic token points to a raw token, and is used by components. A semantic token brings meanings, higher level notions. For example, a raw token can be a “red color”, and a semantic token pointing to it can be a “danger information color”. Semantic tokens are used by components tokens and shared definition of themes. They are splitted in kind of families, i.e. borders, dimensions, colors, spacings, elevations, sizings, opacities, grids and typographies. For some of theses tokens, like for borders, subfamilies can be defined likes width, radius and style. Finally, any of these raw tokens is associated to a raw value which will be - in the end - applied to SwiftUI views inside components. Type aliases will help to make a simple math between any semantic tokens and raw tokens. Thus if we need for example to change a warning color, supposing this color is defined as a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic token","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", we only have to change its assigned value and all components using the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic token","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" won’t be impacted in their definition, only their rendering."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition, there are hundreds of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"semantics tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and we needed to add them to the abstract root theme using extensions for clarity reasons to prevent to have a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift class"}]},{"type":"text","text":" with thousands of lines. Each "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"raw token"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" “family” is then declared in its dedicated "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift protocol"}]},{"type":"text","text":" any root theme must implement. Because we choose to split responsabilities and objects into their own modules, we faced troubles to make possible for children themes to override properties declared in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"protocols"}]},{"text":" and defined in ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"extensions"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the reason why tokens are exposed as ","type":"text"},{"code":"@objc open","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be available and overridable anywhere."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To keep the same semantics as the ones used in our specifications, ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"typealias"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are used to as to make the links to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"primitive types","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and our logic of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"tokens","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":". These type aliases are available for those who want to make their own theme. It’s only syntaxic sugar to bring "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"design words","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in our product."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example with "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/colorsemantictokens","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Declare the semantic tokens","protocol ColorSemanticTokens {","","    var colorBgPrimary: ColorSemanticToken { get }","    var colorBgSecondary: ColorSemanticToken { get }","    var colorBgTertiary: ColorSemanticToken { get }","    \/\/ ...","}","","\/\/ Define the semantic tokens exposed through the theme","extension OUDSTheme: ColorSemanticTokens {","","    \/\/ Color is available in the module of OUDSTheme","    @objc open var colorBgPrimary: ColorSemanticToken { ColorRawTokens.colorFunctionalWhite }","","    \/\/ If the semantic token refers to a raw token not stored in the OUDSTheme module, override later and throw error because unxpected state if used","    @objc open var colorBgSecondary: ColorSemanticToken { fatalError(\"🤖 Raw token unavailable for colorBgSecondary!\") }","","    \/\/ Possible to have tokens not defined in lwoer level must only in themes implementation, throw error if used because unexpected state","    @objc open var colorBgTertiary: ColorSemanticToken { fatalError(\"🤖 No value defined for colorBgTertiary!\") }","}","","\/\/ Add missing values","extension OrangeTheme: ColorSemanticTokens {","","    \/\/ Define value value with the accessible token ","    @objc open var colorBgSecondary: ColorSemanticToken { OrangeBrandColorRawTokens.colorOrange200 }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Important-notice","text":"Important notice"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You may see the source code can be more simple, or the source code does not follow the Swift guidelines, or plenty of warnings of SwiftLint are disabled, or things are dirty.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In fact, rely to much on ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and how the design system is implemented.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There are thousands of tokens, and we do now know if they will be used, how and by whom. In addition, the logic behind these tokens, their nature and names, is very tight to the web domain because the design team behind is more used to web environment than mobileones like Android and iOS. Some tokens like composite tokens are defined in ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" but "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is not able to manage them, it is tinkering, and the outputed JSON cannot manage that too.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"type":"text","text":" exposts the tokens in JSON, which is then parsed with our own fork and implementation of "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"style dictionary"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" tool which struggles to outputs the JSON to web, Kotlin and Swift assets.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the reason why:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"some ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftLint","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" warnings on tokens are disabled: not possible to have doc of public tokens, too long names, too long lines, too long body, too long identifiers"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"some tokens do not have full names, e.g. “colorBackground” are named “colorBg”"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"somes tokens are defined without attached values, thus we throw "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fatalError"},{"text":" because that state is not relevant","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"some tokens in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"text":" use colors defined in another module, thus we throw ","type":"text"},{"code":"fatalError","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to force themes to override with the good and avaialble values"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"we have thousands of tokens, as thousands of tokens are defined"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"we do not know if there is dead code because API are public","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Feel free to send issues and contact us for further details or if you spotted something interesting.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Raw-tokens","text":"Raw tokens","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"What they are","level":3,"anchor":"What-they-are","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Raw tokens"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") are smallest "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" possible. They are associated to raw values and will be finaly the values assigned to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"components","type":"text"}]},{"text":" properties.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In fact, we choose to use as most as possible primitive types for raw values, like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGFloat"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"text":" so as to handle the smallest types with few impacts on the memory for ecodesign principles. Indeed with hundreds of raw tokens, it will be more efficient to store primitive small types than ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"structs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"classes"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"So we expose also in higher level some properties so as to convert when needed some of these types to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" types (like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Font.Weight"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Color"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To keep the same semantics as the ones used in our specifications, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"typealias","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" are used to as to make the links to "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"primitive types","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and our logic of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":". These type aliases are available for those who want to make their own theme."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using more simple and primitive types will help also to test the library. With also type aliases we force users to use our types and not higher level types like "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftUI","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" types."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We also choose to add in ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"extension","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" all the tokens values in a separated file so as to help the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"text":"-JSON-to-Swift parser to build files to copy and past easily in the project and keeping all the other objects.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example for "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/colorrawtokens","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Define type alias for color raw tokens, we don't care in higher level their real type, just use aliases","public typealias ColorRawToken = String","","public enum ColorRawTokens { } ","","extension ColorRawTokens { \/\/ Gathers all color raw tokens, use enums for namespace optimization with static let","","    public static let colorFunctionalWhite: ColorRawToken = \"#FFFFFF\"","    public static let colorTransparentBlack0: ColorRawToken = apply(opacity: OpacityRawTokens.opacity0, on: colorFunctionalBlack)","    ...","}","","extension String { \/\/ The OUDS library still exposes this comptuer property","    public var color: Color {","        Color(hexadecimalCode: self)","    }","}","","\/\/ Themes can embed their own tokens","enum OrangeBrandColorRawTokens {","    public static let colorOrange200: ColorOrangeBrandRawToken = \"#FFC18A\"","}"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Add, edit or remove tokens","anchor":"Add-edit-or-remove-tokens"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to add, edit or remove tokens, you will have to follow some simple steps."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"You may need to "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/issues","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/pulls","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to submit the evolutions you want. Use for example the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Token Update Request","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" issue template.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"For raw tokens","anchor":"For-raw-tokens"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can refer to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensRaw"}]},{"text":" documentation or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"get it online","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"get it online"},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/0-%E2%80%90-How-to-update-tokens","isActive":true},{"text":" also.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"For semantic tokens","type":"heading","anchor":"For-semantic-tokens","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can refer to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},{"text":" documentation or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"get it online","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"get it online","type":"text"}],"isActive":true},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wiki provides details"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/0-%E2%80%90-How-to-update-tokens","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"The wiki provides details"},{"type":"text","text":" also."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ouds\/tokens"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Tokens"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Design tokens represent the small, repeated design decisions that make up a design system’s visual style. Tokens replace hard-coded static values, such as hexadecimal codes for color, with self-explanatory names."}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Themes","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Components","doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Modules"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials"}],"references":{"https://github.com/swiftlang/swift-docc/issues/1026":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-docc\/issues\/1026","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-docc\/issues\/1026","type":"link","title":"the issue we submitted","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the issue we submitted"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Components":{"kind":"article","title":"Components","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Components","abstract":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Components","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are defined in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/"},{"text":" target and can be integrated in applications.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/components","role":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Themes":{"title":"Themes","url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/themes","role":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Themes","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Themes","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are applications of specific values for "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"components tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" using in the end ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"raw tokens"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains any relevant "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"semantic tokens","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"component tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" which can be used for components rendering.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}]},{"text":" has also ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" associated to primitive types so as to give to ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"components","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", written with "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI"}]},{"type":"text","text":", the needed values in the suitable type. A "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" can add for itself any new "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/ouds-ios/wiki/0-%E2%80%90-How-to-update-tokens":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/0-%E2%80%90-How-to-update-tokens","title":"The wiki provides details","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wiki provides details"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/0-%E2%80%90-How-to-update-tokens"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenssemantic/colorsemantictokens":{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/colorsemantictokens","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/colorsemantictokens","type":"link","title":"OUDSTokensComponent\/ColorSemanticTokens","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensComponent\/ColorSemanticTokens"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/GettingStarted":{"title":"Getting Started with OUDS","url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/gettingstarted","role":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/GettingStarted","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"How to add the package as dependency, and import libraries","type":"text"}]},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS/Modules":{"kind":"article","title":"Modules","identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS\/Modules","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"module"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" can be seen as a set of features and components to fill a need."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"There is not module yet."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ouds\/modules","role":"article","type":"topic"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokensraw/":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/","title":"OUDSTokensRaw","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensRaw"}],"url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/"},"doc://ouds-ios.OUDS/documentation/OUDS":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ouds-ios.OUDS\/documentation\/OUDS","title":"OUDS","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ouds","role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"The iOS library of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Orange Unified Design System Design System"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", the new design system unified and cohesive across all platforms to build Orange mobile applications."}],"kind":"symbol"},"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/ouds-ios/blob/develop/OUDS/README.md":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/blob\/develop\/OUDS\/README.md","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/blob\/develop\/OUDS\/README.md","type":"link","title":"README markdown","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"README markdown"}]},"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/ouds-ios/pulls":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/pulls","title":"a pull request","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"a pull request"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/pulls"},"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/ouds-ios/issues":{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/issues","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/issues","type":"link","title":"create an issue","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"create an issue"}]},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokensraw/colorrawtokens":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/colorrawtokens","title":"ColorRawTokens","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ColorRawTokens"}],"url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/colorrawtokens"},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenscomponent/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/","url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenscomponent\/","type":"link","title":"OUDSComponents","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSComponents"}]},"https://ios.unified-design-system.orange.com/documentation/oudstokenssemantic/":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/","title":"OUDSTokensSemantic","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}],"url":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/"}}}